    "It is worth noting that threat vectors may only sometimes be apparent and can come from different sources, such as government actors who may demand existing data or compel organizations to implement new technical measures.",
    "Furthermore, insider risk is also a relevant factor, and mitigating it requires additional protection mechanisms.",
    "Communicating the impact of noise: When a system deliberately adds random noise to results to satisfy DP, it can be challenging for non-experts to understand its reasoning.",
    "1 However, it can also lead to some unexpected outcomes.",
    "For instance, adding noise to a count can generate negative values, and noise may create results not present in the original data set, or some outcomes may be excluded due to counts not reaching a certain threshold."
